{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"11e89f91-ae66-4661-bdae-225dbe9bd8c9","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload for the testing platform works through the **direct runner** (`dotnet run`), not through `dotnet test`. When you run with:\n\n```\nTESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1 dotnet run\n```\n\nthe test host stays alive and watches for file changes, re-running affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` launches a fresh process, runs tests once, and exits — it doesn't support the hot-reload loop.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"039f8c02-a738-41b0-8ca4-f276b5e13313","outputTokens":120,"requestId":"0847:2B9ABB:161DF0A:1781E81:6A045FD6"},"id":"0517ec8d-3699-4920-a92a-80b71dee30b9","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:20.844Z","parentId":"4fadf553-66c2-47fa-846a-eeaad33e704c"}
